description.narrative: UNICEF supported continuity of essential nutrition services such as infant and IYCF and IMAM despite the COVID-19 pandemic. Around 162,830 caregivers of children aged 0-23 months reached with messages aiming to protect breastfeeding in the context of COVID-19. The standardization and integration of nutrition into the mobile clinic and community health volunteer package as well as partnership with Ethnic Health Organizations were important milestones in improving access to nutrition services for vulnerable groups. Although only 22 per cent of Humanitarian Action for Children (HAC) target have been met, assessing the bottlenecks and COVID-19 impact will inform development of scale-up plan. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
